Package: causalworkflows
Title: A Framework for Multi-Component and Staged Causal Estimators
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Sperger", "John", , "josp@duck.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
  )
Description: Provides a framework for estimating causal effects using
    multi-stage, modular modeling procedures. The package introduces the
    'causal_workflow' and 'staged_workflow' objects, which allow for
    flexible specification of nuisance models (e.g., for propensity scores
    and outcome models) and the final causal model. It leverages
    cross-fitting to mitigate the risks of over-fitting when constructing
    estimators like the Augmented Inverse Propensity Weighting (AIPW)
    estimator. This structure is designed to be extensible to other
    multi-stage estimators, such as those used in Q-learning.
